    • Method Detail

      • onImageResults

        void onImageResults(List<Face> faces,
                  Frame image,
                  float timeStamp)
        Delivers information about an image which has been handled by the Detector
        Parameters:
        faces - a list of Face objects containing metrics about each face found in the image. If the image was not processed by the Detector (e.g. if using CameraDetector and the image was not processed due to max FPS settings), faces will be null. If the image was processed but no face was found faces will be a zero length list, and if there were one or more faces found in the image, there will be one element in the list. Returning data for multiple faces in an image is not yet supported.
        image - the image that was processed.
        timeStamp - For FrameDetector, CameraDetector, and VideoFileDetector, this is the time into the frame sequence for the current frame, relative to the starting frame of the sequence. For PhotoDetector, this value will always be 0.
